cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with artwork identification using images captured by mobile phones and wearable cameras. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new dataset and presents baselines using a recent approach that aligns per-class scatter matrices of the source and target CNN streams. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with images and exhibits from museums. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper discusses the goal of stimulating research in few-shot learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with domain adaptation and proposes a new dataset for research in this area.
